cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on wireless sensor networks and proposes a protocol for data aggregation and energy conservation, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The proposed protocol involves clustering and multi-layered architecture, which are key concepts in distributed and cluster computing.
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the use of data aggregation mechanisms in large-scale sensor networks, which involves the use of algorithms and data structures for efficient processing and storage of data.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The proposed protocol aims to prolong the lifetime of the network by optimizing energy consumption, which is a control problem in systems engineering.
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the proposed protocol may have implications for security and privacy in sensor networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
